p_0 = \mathbb{P}( X\mod 3 \equiv 0)
p_1 = \mathbb{P}( X\mod 3 \equiv 1)
p_2 = \mathbb{P}( X\mod 3 \equiv 2)
p_0+p_1+p_2=1
\mathbb{P}( X + Y + Z \mod 3 \equiv 0) = p_0^3 + p_1^3 + p_2^3 + 6 p_0 p_1 p_2
